Film4.uk.title: The Last Stand
Film4.uk.description: (2013) Thriller starring Arnold Schwarzenegger, Johnny Knoxville and Forest Whitaker. A small-town sheriff and his inexperienced staff take on a drug cartel boss who's fleeing to Mexico.

Film4.uk.title: Legion
Film4.uk.description: (2010) Apocalyptic action-horror starring Paul Bettany. God's patience runs out and He decides to wipe humanity from the face of the Earth. Can a rebel archangel save us?

Film4.uk.title: Dead Presidents
Film4.uk.description: (1995) Crime drama set in the Bronx of the 70s, starring Larenz Tate. To support his young family, a Vietnam veteran is driven to take part in the daring robbery of an armoured truck.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Jingle All the Way
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Brian Levant's festive all-action comedy. Arnold Schwarzenegger is on a mission to get his son (Jake Lloyd) the must-have Christmas toy, Turbo Man. But it's sold out everywhere...

Film4.uk.title: Patrick
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Feel-good British family comedy. Sarah's (Beattie Edmondson) chaotic life gets even more complicated when she inherits a naughty pug from her nan.

Film4.uk.title: Film4 Interview Programmes:...
Film4.uk.description: ...Talking Film: Stars and directors talk about the experience of making movies in this compendium of personal and practical reflections.

Film4.uk.title: Turner & Hooch
Film4.uk.description: (1989) Comedy-thriller starring Tom Hanks. A cop investigates a murder to which there's just one witness: Hooch, a slobbering, beer-drinking French mastiff, who now needs 24/7 protection.

Film4.uk.title: Prince Valiant
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Swashbuckling adventure. One of King Arthur's courtiers, the Viking Prince Valiant (Robert Wagner) uncovers the evil Sir Brack's (James Mason) plot to kill the king. Can he foil him?

Film4.uk.title: I, Robot
Film4.uk.description: (2004) Sci-fi thriller with Will Smith. In 2035, a technophobic cop investigates a crime that may have been perpetrated by a robot. Can he keep an open mind?

Film4.uk.title: The Adjustment Bureau
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Romance meets sci-fi thriller. Matt Damon and Emily Blunt star as a politician and a dancer who begin to suspect that a shadowy group of men are interfering with their lives.

Film4.uk.title: Pearl
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Ti West's exuberant retro horror and prequel to X. Mia Goth is Pearl - a twisted Dorothy who wants to dance up the yellow brick road to movie stardom. Can a seedy projectionist help?

Film4.uk.title: X
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Ti West's acclaimed grindhouse horror with Mia Goth. Some adult filmmakers inexplicably choose a ramshackle house in the Bible-Belt wilderness to shoot a film. It's gonna get nasty.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: The Art of Racing in the Rain
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Touching comedy-drama. An ageing golden retriever (voiced by Kevin Costner) tells the story of his life with his best pal, a budding Formula 1 driver.

Film4.uk.title: Think Like a Dog
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Cheeky comedy with Megan Fox. A young science prodigy (Gabriel Bateman) invents a piece of tech that lets him and his pet dog communicate with each other telepathically.

Film4.uk.title: Sword of Sherwood Forest
Film4.uk.description: (1960) Adventure with Richard Greene, Peter Cushing and a young Oliver Reed. Can Robin Hood foil the villainous Sheriff of Nottingham's evil plan to murder the Archbishop of Canterbury?

Film4.uk.title: Film4 Interview Programmes:...
Film4.uk.description: ...Talking Film: Stars and directors talk about making movies in this compendium of personal and practical reflections. Features Danny Boyle, Amy Schumer, Chiwetel Ejiofor and more.

Film4.uk.title: Rat Race
Film4.uk.description: (2001) Comedy. A Las Vegas casino-owner sets up a unique game for six punters: a race across America, hunting for $2m. Starring John Cleese, Rowan Atkinson and Whoopi Goldberg.

Film4.uk.title: The Greatest Showman
Film4.uk.description: (2017) Hugh Jackman, Zac Efron and Michelle Williams star in the Golden-Globe-winning, toe-tapping smash hit musical about the life and times of P.T. Barnum, who created the circus.

Film4.uk.title: The Equalizer 2
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Action crime thriller sequel. Denzel Washington returns as Robert McCall, who's out for revenge after ruthless killers murder an agency contact who he also considered a friend.

Film4.uk.title: The Integrity of Joseph Chambers
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Robert Machoian's drama ponders the state of modern masculinity as a cack-handed insurance salesman played by Clayne Crawford heads solo to the woods for a fateful hunting trip.

Film4.uk.title: First Love
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Takashi Miike's gory, violent crime-thriller. Budding boxer Leo helps a woman who's been forced into sex work but gets more than he bargained for. In Japanese/subs.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Erika Jones meets gay rugby player Wayne Sharples to find out about some of the challenges he's faced growing up and why he has such a passion for his chosen sport. [SL]

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: D-Day the Sixth of June
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Wartime romance set against the background of the D-Day landings, starring Robert Taylor and Dana Wynter. A married American officer embarks on an affair with English nurse.

Film4.uk.title: Rio Grande
Film4.uk.description: (1950) Western. John Wayne plays the commander of a Texan fort at which his ex-wife (Maureen O'Hara) pitches up. Can he win back her love by saving kidnapped children from Apache raiders?

Film4.uk.title: Buchanan Rides Alone
Film4.uk.description: (1958) Western. Randolph Scott stars as a drifter who arrives in a small border town and tangles with a group of villains after helping a wealthy young Mexican, played by Manuel Rojas.

Film4.uk.title: Film4 Interview Programmes:...

Film4.uk.title: Earth vs the Flying Saucers
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Sci-fi thriller. Hugh Marlowe stars as a scientist who discovers Earth is threatened by a fleet of flying saucers bent on global conquest. With special effects by Ray Harryhausen.

Film4.uk.title: Entrapment
Film4.uk.description: (1999) Action thriller starring Sean Connery as Robert 'Mac' MacDougal, one of the world's finest art thieves, and Catherine Zeta-Jones as the insurance company agent out to trap him.

Film4.uk.title: Mission: Impossible - Rogue Nation
Film4.uk.description: (2015) Part five of the Tom Cruise action-thriller franchise. The secret agents must bring down a terrorist group, but that's not easy when the CIA are hunting you down...

Film4.uk.title: A Most Wanted Man
Film4.uk.description: (2014) Thriller with Philip Seymour Hoffman. The arrival of a refugee in Hamburg sparks a flurry of intelligence activity. Is he an asylum seeker or a terrorist? Strong language/violence.
